A bank employee (39) from Mtubatuba, northern KZN, and her accomplice (21) appeared at the Richards Bay regional court on Friday charged with fraud. It’s alleged that Hlengiwe Ntshangase transferred cash from clients who had fixed deposit accounts without their authorisation. Her accomplice, Nelisiwe Mkhwanazi, was also arrested. The state alleges that various bank accounts were created using Ntshangase’s particulars and other accomplices. Police said that Ntshangase was employed as a trainee at one of the banks at Mtubatuba. Over R1.1 million was allegedly transferred into the newly created accounts. Hawks spokesperson, Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo, said a case of fraud was reported at the Mtubatuba Police Station. “The case docket was allocated to Hawks members for further investigations. They were arrested and briefly appeared in the Richards Bay regional court.” Ntshangase was granted R20 000 bail while Mkhwanazi was released on warning. The matter was postponed to March 15. Police said more arrests are expected.